raceComments: {"comment":"4. INVINCIBLE WOMAN was good enough to win on debut as a juvenile before failing in the Listed Magic Millions juvenile classic, before having a spell. She resumes after throat surgery and is ready to rumble after winning a recent jumpout. Watch the market moves. 1. SONOFKIRK has been freshened up after a sound effort for fifth in the G3 McNeil Stakes at Caulfield in late August. He has been close up in a couple of jumpouts, and with the blinkers on for the first time, he can take this out. 2. CAVALRY GIRL held on bravely to score at Mornington nearly 4 weeks ago after leading all the way. She missed the kick that day, which makes that effort even better, and with the same weight to carry, she can repeat the dose. 5. BOLD SECRET caught the eye in his only run as a juvenile late last season, and a recent jumpout has kept him ticking along. He is big on ability, and if 1000m is not too short for him, he will be very competitive. Each-way value.","runners":[4,1,2,5],"exclusive":true}
